We used Carbon catering for our wedding rehearsal dinner, and it was a huge success. I ordered dinner for 40 about 5 weeks before the event. There were many options to personalize the meal, to get exactly when we wanted.  I opted for the “Classic Catering” option with steak, chicken, and fajita veggies. It came with flour and corn tortillas, onions, cheese, lettuce, tomatoes, cilantro, flour and corn tortilla chips, several kinds of salsa, and MORE! We also ordered guacamole, which was a huge hit! I ordered the exact number of servings for the number of people at the event, and I had 1.5 trays of meat and TONS of toppings left over (best lunches EVER). Plan more than one 6 ft table to serve the food.  Every single guest RAVED about the food - everything was fresh, hot, and delicious. I had guests who were vegetarian, vegan, and steak-lovers, and every single one of them LOVED the options that Carbon provided us.  The only thing that didn’t go off perfectly was the paper plates- we ran out of plates after everyone had their first plate. Especially since there were chips/salsa/guacamole, we could have used more plates. It was a minor inconvenience, and I think I was the only one who noticed.
